tools.gsf.navigation.siteplan

Class AbstractAssetNode<N extends AssetNode<N> & ConfigurableNode<N>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • tools.gsf.navigation.siteplan.AbstractAssetNode<N>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, AssetNode<N>, ConfigurableNode<N>, Node<N>

    public abstract class AbstractAssetNode<N extends AssetNode<N> & ConfigurableNode<N>>
extends Object
implements AssetNode<N>, ConfigurableNode<N>
    Simple node, representing an asset, that can be populated with asset data. It is up to the concrete class extending this base class to decide what data to expose and how. This base class just deals with the annoying stuff required by most (all?) AssetNode implementations.
    Since:
    2017-03-02.
    Author:
    Freddy Villalba
    See Also:

        public void removeChildren()
        Description copied from interface: ConfigurableNode

      • removeChild

        public boolean removeChild(N child)
        Description copied from interface: ConfigurableNode
        Breaks the relationship between this node and the specified child, meaning: - This node is not the parent of the specified child anymore. - The removed node is not this node's child anymore. The method returns true if the specified child was removed, false otherwise.
        Specified by:
